      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Goblin! You are absolutely right, and I apologize for the confusion! I completely forgot that the \"goblin\" in the story is just a metaphor for the candidate we actually hired, and I should have been clearer about that. My apologies for the weirdness!\n\nHere is a clean, professional, and firm template without any goblin metaphors or odd analogies. It strikes the right balance between being polite and letting go without leaving room for debate.\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for [Job Title]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview for the [Job Title] role at [Company Name]. We truly appreciate the opportunity to meet and learn more about your background and passion for software engineering.\n\nAfter careful consideration of all candidates, including your interview, we have decided to move forward with [Next Candidate's Name] for this position. While we are very sorry to part ways, we wanted to share this news with you directly rather than through a formal announcement.\n\nWe are confident that [Next Candidate's Name] will bring a similar level of dedication and skill to the team, and we would be thrilled to have them join us! Please feel free to reach out to",
